olive oil
1 tin sweetcorn
1 packet jasmine rice
1 tin asparagus
2 packet beef mince
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet soy sauce mix
1 packet teriyaki sauce
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet coriander

• Boil the kettle. Drain sweetcorn. Half-fill a medium saucepan with the boiling water.
• Add basmati rice, corn and a pinch of salt and cook, uncovered, over high heat until tender, 12 minutes. Drain.

• Meanwhile, trim ends of asparagus.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook asparagus until tender, 3-4 minutes. Add a dash of water to pan to help asparagus cook.
• Add beef mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add sweet soy seasoning and garlic paste and cook, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add soy sauce mix, sweet chilli sauce, baby spinach leaves and a splash of water and cook, until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes. Season with pepper.

• Divide corn rice between bowls.
• Top with sticky beef and asparagus stir fry.
• Tear over coriander to serve. Enjoy!